#### Recipe for creation of post

#### Framing When To Make A Note

A. Classically, posts will arise through two ways:

1. You will get a thought outside of Obsidian and determine you need to insert it into Obsidian
2. You will be looking at something in an Obsidian post, and it will hit you "this needs to be added"

B. Workflow for non-categorized items that have no obvious linkage

1. All external webpages clipped through Obsidian webclipper should be placed in the Clippings Folder
2. All new note that are not able to be categorized need to fit be placed into the Inbasket Folder
   (See [[Getting Things Done (GTD)]])
3. Both of these are top level folder

#### A2:  "This Needs To Be Added"

Should be the most common operation with this wiki.  You have a thought, and rather than updating the note, because we are doing Atomic Notes, this new thought needs to be placed inside a separate note.  This is done by using \[\[  NEWNOTE    \]\] bracket.  

A2.i:  Type "\[\[ NEWNOTE\]\]" all as one string.  You may need to click off the work to get out of editing of the text.  However, once you click outside of the text, the link becomes hot.  If you click on the link, a note is made, and you are taken to this new note.  Fill in the note.

A2.ii: Type NEWNOTE, then highlight the text, and hit \[\[ on the keyboard.  The word will be bracketed on both sides to create a new note.  Move off the work to be able to click on it for new note just like in A2.i.

#### Backlinks

Most likely if you made a note from another note, they have a linkage.  Therefore, you may want to see where a note was created from.  There are three ways to do this:

1. When you arrive to your new note, type "This note comes from " then press \[\[ and this will bring up a list of recent notes that you've made.  Your old note should be at the top, and you can select it.  Or it also searches all your notes, and you can link through search.
2. Auto show backlinks.  In the setting area, under the gear option, one backlink plugin and turn on bottom links.   See below.  You may need a restart.


![image](data:image/webp;base64,)

#### If Backlink Plugin Enabled

 1. Auto backlink showing sidebar.  Obsidian automatically makes a backlink bookmark, and to see it, you need to have the side backlink bar open.  This will show you all the entry points to the note.  This is shown for this note.
